{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3fbf3775-4e77-45fb-949f-6cf2213e173f","content":"Here's the mapping and the new command:\n\n**Flag equivalents:**\n\n| VSTest (`dotnet test`) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**New command** (MTP args go after `--`):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Required changes in your project:**\n\n1. Add the property to your test `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n   ```\n\n2. Add the NuGet extension packages:\n   ```\n   Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\n   Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\n   Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\n   Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\n   ```\n\nOn .NET 8, `dotnet test` acts as a thin wrapper—everything after `--` is forwarded directly to the MTP test host.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"722509cb-64d5-49a7-a7fe-569994da8033","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` (or using Microsoft.CodeCoverage settings)\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith .NET 8, you can still use `dotnet test` to run MTP-based projects, though the underlying execution differs from the traditional VSTest runner.\n\nFor MTP equivalents, `--filter` works the same way, but logging and coverage collection require specific MTP extensions—`--report-trx` for TRX output and `--collect-coverage` for code coverage, each needing their respective packages.\n\nWith .NET 8, you'd pass these MTP arguments after `--` when running `dotnet test`, combining filters, reporting, coverage collection, and diagnostic dumps all in one command. Refining the command structure for .NET 8 with MTP enabled—the filter and other arguments need to go after the `--` separator since MTP handles them natively. I also need to note the required NuGet packages for trx reporting and code coverage collection.","outputTokens":1582,"requestId":"4810:37A86A:3203119:3699014:69FBE338"},"id":"dda79621-884d-4477-a38c-a53c3b6dd296","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:56:56.158Z","parentId":"70d1007d-be67-4a08-ae73-99bf34fe8176"}
